Three pictures from when we were told to go home this afternoon (~3:30p local), all should be ~640 x 360. I'm not very good at this whole image-attaching thing, so constructive criticism is appreciated I heard from some people on the west side of the building that, much like Frennzy, they saw several lightning strikes behind the mountain and then saw smoke rising. Work smelled delicious when we got kicked out... and if I was a little faster getting to the camera on my phone the first shot would've had a helicopter in it as well.No zoom, I was standing in the driveway of the building when I took this.Surprised when I got home to realize there was a flame in this shot... zoomed in some but still caught the side of the building.I think trees were exploding on the ridge, there was an impressive burst of flame.
