Frennzy wrote:and now...wind stormI was up on Davidson Mesa watching the fire from Louisville (live just a few blocks from there) when the wind blew in. It had the odd effect of making the Flagstaff fire look much smaller than it was, since the smoke almost completely dissipated -- just a thin gray twisting around was left. Then the winds died for a bit, and I could see the smoke curl over the top of one of the flatirons and just seem to weave through the trees as the darker smoke behind it glowed orange. Made me think "oh shit." My poor state. Rain, please.
