I've been at the Air Force Academy since last week and have various pictures of the smoke since the Waldo Canyon fire started last Saturday. I don't have any good shots of the flames since I was a little busy last night. We moved to Peterson AFB after the evacuation. I live on the south side of the Denver area, so I'm not in danger of losing my house. I just don't know where most of my travel 'stuff' is. The person that cleared my room grabbed my laptop and iPad, and luckily my cell phone charger. In the grand scheme of things, not knowing where my clean clothes are is minor compared to what a lot of people are going through.
